data.title: Great dining
data.text: Take a trip down memory lane in maybe the only one left Roy Rogers in NYC. Always loved their salad bar.

data.title: Roy Rogers Sturbridge. MA
data.text:
Roy Rogers has good fried chicken.

The Roy Rogers in Sturbridge, MA is a fast food road house that has over the 20 years I've been eating fried chicken there, provided consistently good hot fried chicken.

Crispy fried chicken is not pretentious, but offers an opporturnity for a genuine American tasty alternative when traveling by car.

The staff are friendly and efficient. They anticipate the arrival lunch crowds and bus travelers so there is no time lost waiting for your food.

Fried chicken isn't diet food either, but why not (?) when you're traveling by car.

I heartily recommend the Roy Rogers on the Mass Pike at Sturbridge. 

PS, the biscuits are good too!

data.title: Recomendado
data.text: Recomiendo este lugar si quieres comer algo basico pero totalmente tracional, la tipica comida rapida americana (papas con chedar)
